      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "Minimum wage hikes are a common regulatory hurdle that small businesses must navigate, regardless of their location. While proponents argue it helps workers, these increases inevitably raise operational costs for small shops. In rural areas, where margins are already tight, these hikes can force businesses to either raise prices or reduce staff, which is a direct consequence of increased labor costs. Ultimately, it puts pressure on local economies to adapt to higher labor expenses.",
